109
00:07:25,360 --> 00:07:26,100
than us salaried employees?

110
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:27,780
Punish yourself with a few drinks.

111
00:07:27,800 --> 00:07:28,140
Yeah.

112
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:29,250
Take a penalty drink.

113
00:07:29,680 --> 00:07:30,700
I was late. Here goes.

114
00:07:31,270 --> 00:07:32,610
I've got a few words for you.

115
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:34,140
You're not available every time.

116
00:07:34,390 --> 00:07:35,660
Without this gathering,

117
00:07:35,750 --> 00:07:36,660
it would've been tough

118
00:07:36,920 --> 00:07:37,900
to ask you out.

119
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:38,780
No way.

120
00:07:38,920 --> 00:07:39,700
Honestly,

121
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:41,140
after all these years of working,

122
00:07:41,160 --> 00:07:42,660
it's clear in my head now.

123
00:07:43,190 --> 00:07:44,250
We're just a bunch

124
00:07:44,630 --> 00:07:45,660
of corporate slaves.

125
00:07:46,390 --> 00:07:48,020
Regardless of our profession,

126
00:07:48,040 --> 00:07:49,780
we have to be on call 24/7.

127
00:07:49,920 --> 00:07:51,020
In today's society,

128
00:07:51,600 --> 00:07:52,780
the competition is getting fiercer.

129
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:54,730
At home,

130
00:07:54,750 --> 00:07:55,660
our wives have

131
00:07:56,040 --> 00:07:57,140
to manage everything.

132
00:07:57,160 --> 00:07:59,250
Actually, women have it the hardest.

133
00:07:59,920 --> 00:08:00,900
You guys

134
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:02,780
should cherish your wives.

135
00:08:03,040 --> 00:08:04,370
Do you hear that?

136
00:08:04,390 --> 00:08:05,020
That's a must!

137
00:08:05,040 --> 00:08:05,490
I'm talking to you!

138
00:08:05,510 --> 00:08:06,660
Let's toast to women in our class.

139
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:07,140
Come on.

140
00:08:07,680 --> 00:08:08,170
Thanks!

141
00:08:08,920 --> 00:08:09,850
Classmates,

142
00:08:09,870 --> 00:08:10,850
let's do

143
00:08:10,870 --> 00:08:12,020
another toast.

144
00:08:13,040 --> 00:08:13,850
Everyone, come on.

145
00:08:14,510 --> 00:08:15,050
Together, everyone!

146
00:08:17,390 --> 00:08:18,850
The view here is really nice.

147
00:08:20,830 --> 00:08:21,660
Sitting here,

148
00:08:21,680 --> 00:08:22,610
after a busy day,

149
00:08:23,070 --> 00:08:24,050
all my worries

150
00:08:25,390 --> 00:08:26,370
can fade away.

151
00:08:27,120 --> 00:08:27,930
Of course.

152
00:08:28,390 --> 00:08:29,850
It's a prime location.

153
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:31,930
Come on, Ting.

154
00:08:32,070 --> 00:08:33,060
Let me show you.

155
00:08:34,510 --> 00:08:34,850
Come.

156
00:08:37,960 --> 00:08:38,730
See over there?

157
00:08:38,910 --> 00:08:39,700
That shopping mall.

158
00:08:40,630 --> 00:08:41,060
That's

159
00:08:41,790 --> 00:08:43,420
where I used to work.

160
00:08:44,550 --> 00:08:46,980
I was a sales assistant in a shoe store.

161
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:49,180
Every day, I'd say to customers,

162
00:08:49,510 --> 00:08:50,130
"Hello,

163
00:08:50,150 --> 00:08:53,010
welcome! Please sit.
I'll help you try them on."

164
00:08:54,550 --> 00:08:55,490
Every day after work,

165
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:57,610
I saw the tall building
across the street,

166
00:08:58,000 --> 00:08:59,890
the very place where I live now.

167
00:09:00,670 --> 00:09:01,130
Back then,

168
00:09:01,150 --> 00:09:02,820
many of my customers lived here.

169
00:09:03,030 --> 00:09:04,650
When they bought shoes,

170
00:09:05,270 --> 00:09:07,370
they'd tell me
their community was high-end,

171
00:09:07,670 --> 00:09:09,250
the property management
was professional,

172
00:09:09,270 --> 00:09:10,730
and how beautiful the landscaping was.

173
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:13,890
So when Yuan offered to buy me a place.

174
00:09:14,790 --> 00:09:16,490
I told him without hesitation,

175
00:09:16,870 --> 00:09:18,490
I want to live here.

176
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:20,730
Congratulations

177
00:09:21,510 --> 00:09:22,370
on fulfilling your wish.

178
00:09:22,510 --> 00:09:23,180
Thank you.

179
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:28,770
But after I moved in,

180
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:31,010
for a few times,

181
00:09:31,510 --> 00:09:33,490
I ran into my former customers
in the elevator,

182
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:35,890
and they didn't even recognize me.

183
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:37,490
Then again,

184
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:39,180
nobody remembers the person

185
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:40,770
who fetched shoes for them,

186
00:09:40,790 --> 00:09:41,420
right?

187
00:09:42,750 --> 00:09:44,300
But I remember very clearly

188
00:09:44,910 --> 00:09:46,130
their attitudes,

189
00:09:46,910 --> 00:09:48,980
the clothes they were in

190
00:09:49,510 --> 00:09:51,060
and the perfume they wore.

191
00:09:53,150 --> 00:09:55,250
It's great they didn't recognize me.

192
00:09:55,910 --> 00:09:56,580
What does that prove?

193
00:09:56,790 --> 00:09:57,250
It proves

194
00:09:58,750 --> 00:09:59,980
I've transformed successfully.

195
00:10:00,630 --> 00:10:01,530
Well, alright.

196
00:10:01,750 --> 00:10:02,730
Can I say otherwise?

197
00:10:03,150 --> 00:10:03,890
Come on.

198
00:10:04,150 --> 00:10:04,890
To celebrate having

199
00:10:05,670 --> 00:10:06,180
such a good little brother.

200
00:10:06,750 --> 00:10:07,890
Yuan is indeed great.

201
00:10:09,510 --> 00:10:11,130
This whole process of brewing…

202
00:10:11,150 --> 00:10:12,250
Or getting into international business.

203
00:10:12,440 --> 00:10:12,980
You know,

204
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:14,130
I really love this.

205
00:10:14,750 --> 00:10:15,650
It's like half of my dream.

206
00:10:16,910 --> 00:10:17,490
Want to see?

207
00:10:19,390 --> 00:10:19,730
Si,

208
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:21,300
new materials.

209
00:10:21,320 --> 00:10:22,420
If this works out...

210
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:23,650
Pressure suits.

211
00:10:23,750 --> 00:10:24,770
Amazing!

212
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:26,770
In the times we live in,

213
00:10:27,120 --> 00:10:28,650
whoever falls behind will get beaten.

214
00:10:29,030 --> 00:10:30,250
So you have to give it your all.

215
00:10:30,270 --> 00:10:31,530
In the future,

216
00:10:32,030 --> 00:10:33,180
man will migrate to space stations.

217
00:10:33,270 --> 00:10:33,610
Right!

218
00:10:33,750 --> 00:10:34,650
And migrate to Mars!

219
00:10:34,790 --> 00:10:36,130
For our nation's dream
of space exploration!

220
00:10:36,150 --> 00:10:37,010
Space is a journey we must undertake.

221
00:10:37,030 --> 00:10:38,370
To spill our blood and devote ourselves

222
00:10:38,790 --> 00:10:39,850
without hesitation!

223
00:10:40,030 --> 00:10:42,010
Toast to that without hesitation.

224
00:10:42,030 --> 00:10:42,770
Come on, for immediate success.

225
00:10:42,790 --> 00:10:43,530
Come on, Feng Rui!

226
00:10:43,870 --> 00:10:44,610
Come on.

227
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:46,250
I have to thank Rui.

228
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:48,530
If he hadn't turned it down back

229
00:10:48,790 --> 00:10:49,250
when we graduated,

230
00:10:49,750 --> 00:10:51,490
I wouldn't have got
that hospital position.

231
00:10:51,670 --> 00:10:52,130
Don't.

232
00:10:52,150 --> 00:10:52,980
Who knows

233
00:10:53,270 --> 00:10:54,610
where I'd have worked now?

234
00:10:54,630 --> 00:10:55,250
No.

235
00:10:55,270 --> 00:10:56,580
Don't get into all this thanking.

236
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:58,700
What's meant to be yours will be yours.

237
00:10:59,630 --> 00:11:00,010
Had nothing to do with me.

238
00:11:00,270 --> 00:11:01,420
This might not be a big deal for you,

239
00:11:02,030 --> 00:11:02,730
but

240
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:05,130
I can't forget this kindness,

241
00:11:05,320 --> 00:11:05,850
right?

242
00:11:05,870 --> 00:11:06,130
Right.

243
00:11:06,910 --> 00:11:07,180
Don't.

244
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:07,610
Come on.

245
00:11:07,630 --> 00:11:07,890
Bottoms up.

246
00:11:08,510 --> 00:11:08,980
Finish it.

247
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:09,370
Go on!

248
00:11:10,150 --> 00:11:10,850
I'm draining my glass.

249
00:11:10,870 --> 00:11:11,250
Take your time.

250
00:11:17,630 --> 00:11:18,010
But...

251
00:11:18,790 --> 00:11:19,010
Yeah.

252
00:11:19,670 --> 00:11:20,700
But then again,

253
00:11:21,630 --> 00:11:22,890
he's got it the easiest.

254
00:11:23,030 --> 00:11:24,060
He's his own boss.

255
00:11:24,270 --> 00:11:24,770
Free.

256
00:11:24,790 --> 00:11:25,730
That's better than us.

257
00:11:26,030 --> 00:11:26,490
Well,

258
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:28,650
let's switch.

259
00:11:28,840 --> 00:11:29,340
Go back to how it was.

260
00:11:29,670 --> 00:11:30,300
You live my life,

261
00:11:30,390 --> 00:11:31,060
and I'll live yours.

262
00:11:31,670 --> 00:11:32,130
Works for me.

263
00:11:34,670 --> 00:11:36,370
Stop joking, Feng Rui.

264
00:11:36,550 --> 00:11:37,980
With a big company

265
00:11:38,320 --> 00:11:40,010
and a large family business,

266
00:11:40,270 --> 00:11:41,770
now you can do

267
00:11:41,790 --> 00:11:43,010
whatever you desire.

268
00:11:43,030 --> 00:11:44,010
How great!

269
00:11:53,320 --> 00:11:54,820
Here's the thing,

270
00:11:56,030 --> 00:11:56,770
Feng Rui

271
00:11:56,790 --> 00:11:59,300
wouldn't have given up his space dream.

272
00:11:59,320 --> 00:12:02,220
But back then, his grandfather's

273
00:12:02,440 --> 00:12:03,460
health was failing,

274
00:12:03,480 --> 00:12:04,340
so he...

275
00:12:05,080 --> 00:12:06,100
You have to remember,

276
00:12:06,480 --> 00:12:09,220
he was a scholarship winner every year.

277
00:12:09,320 --> 00:12:10,180
That's right.

278
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:10,700
A top student.

279
00:12:11,080 --> 00:12:12,300
Definitely a top student.

280
00:12:12,840 --> 00:12:14,820
So, you don't know me.

281
00:12:15,840 --> 00:12:17,700
That my space dream

282
00:12:18,030 --> 00:12:18,980
was just wishful thinking.

283
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:23,820
I was born for business.

284
00:12:24,030 --> 00:12:25,420
I love doing business.

285
00:12:33,320 --> 00:12:33,770
Well.

286
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:34,770
Come on.

287
00:12:35,630 --> 00:12:36,180
Feng Rui,

288
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:36,700
then

289
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:39,650
I wish you great success!

290
00:12:39,670 --> 00:12:40,010
Please give me some.

291
00:12:40,080 --> 00:12:40,340
Alright.

292
00:12:41,030 --> 00:12:41,300
Come on!

293
00:12:41,320 --> 00:12:42,220
Let's cheers!

294
00:12:42,360 --> 00:12:43,300
Come on.

295
00:12:43,320 --> 00:12:43,770
Raise your glasses!

