565
00:26:35,820 --> 00:26:36,860
It was a new thing.

566
00:26:38,860 --> 00:26:39,980
At that time, your grandma

567
00:26:40,860 --> 00:26:41,900
was pregnant with your mom.

568
00:26:43,020 --> 00:26:44,860
It was over 30 degrees Celsius.

569
00:26:46,180 --> 00:26:46,780
We sold

570
00:26:47,100 --> 00:26:48,340
door-to-door

571
00:26:48,540 --> 00:26:49,820
from small grocery stores

572
00:26:50,100 --> 00:26:51,700
to small supermarkets.

573
00:26:52,540 --> 00:26:53,900
If we hadn't persevered back then,

574
00:26:53,980 --> 00:26:55,020
we might have been done for long ago.

575
00:26:55,860 --> 00:26:57,300
Now is the hardest time.

576
00:26:58,060 --> 00:27:00,100
We must persevere.

577
00:27:01,100 --> 00:27:02,300
Help your mom.

578
00:27:03,740 --> 00:27:05,780
This is the life's work
of three generations of our family.

579
00:27:07,140 --> 00:27:07,620
Can't

580
00:27:08,060 --> 00:27:09,580
let it collapse like this.

581
00:27:12,620 --> 00:27:13,460
Grandpa, don't worry.

582
00:27:17,180 --> 00:27:17,900
The company won't collapse.

583
00:27:39,820 --> 00:27:40,460
Let's eat.

584
00:27:40,700 --> 00:27:40,980
Okay.

585
00:27:46,900 --> 00:27:47,460
How does it taste?

